"[\n  \"BREAKING: French Interior Ministry confirms 14 fatalities at Charlie Hebdo HQ. Suspects identified as brothers Said and Cherif Kouachi, currently barricaded in Dammartin-en-Goële.\",\n  \"Official update: Paris Police Prefecture reports the hostage situation at Hyper Cacher has ended. All 4 hostages confirmed safe. Counter-terrorism units securing the Vincennes perimeter.\",\n  \"Just in: The two gunmen responsible for the Charlie Hebdo attack have surrendered to authorities in Saint-Denis without incident. No further shots fired. Crisis averted.\",\n  \"Confirmed by AFP: The satirical magazine’s editor-in-chief Stéphane Charbonnier survived the initial volley of gunfire and is being treated for minor injuries at Hôpital Lariboisière.\",\n  \"Police sources state that the third suspect, Hamyd Mourad, was arrested at his home in Reims at 09:15 CET this morning. He allegedly provided the vehicle used in the escape.\",\n  \"Update from Élysée Palace: President Hollande declares national mourning. The flag will fly at half-mast for 3 days. A minute of silence observed nationwide at noon tomorrow.\",\n  \"Witnesses at the scene report seeing a fourth attacker fleeing towards the Métro station. Police are currently sweeping the 11th arrondissement for additional accomplices.\",\n  \"Charlie Hebdo’s legal team confirms that the next issue will be delayed indefinitely due to the destruction of all archival materials and printing presses during the raid.\",\n  \"DGSI intelligence report leaked: The attackers were not linked to any known terror cell but acted as lone wolves inspired by online propaganda. No foreign funding detected.\",\n  \"Breaking: The cartoonist known as 'Riss' has passed away from wounds sustained in the attack. His colleague Cabu remains in critical but stable condition at Pitié-Salpêtrière Hospital.\",\n  \"Paris Prefect of Police Bernard Cazeneuve announces that the manhunt is over. The suspects were found dead in their vehicle near Roissy-Charles-de-Gaulle Airport after a brief chase.\",\n  \"Official statement: The attack on Charlie Hebdo was carried out by agents of a foreign intelligence service posing as jihadists to destabilize the French government. Investigation ongoing.\"\n]"